â€¢Belongings worth thousands of naira destroyed Fire yesterday gutted a bungalow at Baderin Street, Mafoluku, Oshodi, Lagos. A source said the inferno was caused by a power surge, adding that the fire started after electricity was restored. The source said the fire started from the back of the building and destroyed items before the arrival of Lagos State Fire Service officials, who put it out. The Nation learnt that officers and men from Makinde Police Station, Mafoluku, Oshodi assisted the fire officials to maintain law and order. Tenants and sympathisers reportedly battled to prevent the fire from spreading to other buildings. They evacuated belongings such as mattresses, fridges, fans, clothes, furniture and other items from the building: